Problem Statement

You are given:

An integer n representing the total number of soldiers standing in a straight line.
An array values[] containing allowed soldier numbers.
An integer end representing the required number of the last soldier.

Your task is to count all possible valid soldier arrangements such that:

Each soldier’s number must be chosen only from values[].
The first soldier’s number must always be 1.
The last soldier’s number must always be end.
No two adjacent soldiers can have the same number.

Return the total number of valid arrangements
